TTT Enterprise – Privacy Policy

Last Updated: 2025.11.17

1. General Information

TTT Enterprise (“we”, “our”, “the App”) is committed to protecting the privacy of its users.
This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect information when you use the TTT Enterprise mobile application.

TTT Enterprise is an internal enterprise application designed for employee work management, including attendance tracking, work requests, and internal communication within an organization. The app is intended for authorized users only.

2. Information We Collect

TTT Enterprise collects only the minimum information required to operate core business features.

• Account & Usage Information

We may collect limited user-related data such as:

Employee account identifier (e.g. work email or internal ID)

App usage logs (for system stability and security)

Device type and operating system version

This data is used solely for internal system functionality and security purposes.

• Location Information (Optional)

If location permission is granted, the app may access approximate or device location only at the moment of specific user actions, such as:

Employee check-in / check-out

Attendance verification

Work activity confirmation (if applicable)

Important notes:

Location access is optional

Users may deny location permission and still use the app

The app does not track users continuously

Location data is not collected in the background

Location is not used for marketing or analytics purposes

• Request & Attendance Data

When using attendance or request features, the app may collect:

Selected date and time

Request type (leave, overtime, remote work, etc.)

User-entered notes or attachments (if provided)

The app does not collect:

Payment information

Bank card data

Government-issued identifiers

Biometric data

3. How We Use Your Information

Collected information is used strictly for the following purposes:

Attendance and work activity verification

Processing internal employee requests

Improving system reliability and performance

Ensuring security and preventing unauthorized use

Meeting legal or organizational compliance requirements

We do not use user data for advertising, profiling, or resale.

4. Data Sharing

TTT Enterprise does not sell or rent user data.

Data may be shared only in limited situations:

• Legal Requirements

If required by law, court order, or regulatory authority.

• Internal System Providers

Trusted infrastructure or analytics services may process anonymized technical data strictly to support system operation.

• Security & Fraud Prevention

If suspicious or unauthorized activity is detected, relevant information may be shared with appropriate internal or legal authorities.

5. User Rights

Users have the right to:

Access their stored data (where applicable)

Request correction of inaccurate information

Revoke permissions such as location access

Stop using the application at any time

Most permissions can be managed directly from the device settings.

6. Data Security

We apply reasonable technical and organizational safeguards, including:

Secure communication protocols

Restricted access controls

Encryption where applicable

Regular system and security reviews

While no system can be guaranteed 100% secure, we take data protection seriously and continuously improve our safeguards.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated as system features evolve or legal requirements change.
Significant updates will be communicated through the app or official channels.

